<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FE8FE6648A75669FE2BFD35" pageId="422" pageNumber="423" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FE8FE6648A75669FD9BFD51" blockId="422.[151,1437,325,818]" pageId="422" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE8FE6648A75669FE38FEAE" bold="true" box="[151,413,325,350]" pageId="422" pageNumber="423">Description of female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FE8FE664A575669FD65FEAD" box="[615,704,325,349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="422" pageNumber="423" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Head testaceous-darkened; antenna brown, except segments 1–3 testaceous; mesosoma testaceous; metasoma testaceous-darkened; legs testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 5:4:9:6:5:5:5:5:3:5.5. Head excavated, unsculptured; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; POL = 1; OL = 1; OOL = 6. Palpal formula 4/2. Pronotum shiny, hairy, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Metanotum not hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, completely smooth, with posterior surface transversely striate only near distal apex. Mesopleuron and metapleuron not transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture obsolete. Fore tarsal segments in following proportions: 10:2:3:11:17. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE8FE6649D9556DFDC2FDA9" box="[489,615,577,601]" captionStart="PLATE 132" captionStartId="421.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[228,1376,241,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-64@421.[190,1397,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="421" captionText="PLATE 132. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus thai (from Olmi 1984). B. G. viet (from Olmi 1986). C. G. viraktamathi (from Olmi 1987c). D. G.yasumatsui(from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.15 mm for B, 0.37 mm for C and 0.22 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278840/files/figure.png" pageId="422" pageNumber="423">Plate 132B</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and seven peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FE8FE6649205549FE2BFD8D" box="[272,398,613,637]" captionStart="PLATE 132" captionStartId="421.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[228,1376,241,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-64@421.[190,1397,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="421" captionText="PLATE 132. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus thai (from Olmi 1984). B. G. viet (from Olmi 1986). C. G. viraktamathi (from Olmi 1987c). D. G.yasumatsui(from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.15 mm for B, 0.37 mm for C and 0.22 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278840/files/figure.png" pageId="422" pageNumber="423">Plate 132B</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally not serrated, with one row of 15 lamellae; distal apex with about ten lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418FE8FE6648F75581FE2BFD35" blockId="422.[151,1437,325,818]" box="[199,398,685,709]" pageId="422" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FE8FE6648F75581FEAEFD35" bold="true" box="[199,267,685,709]" pageId="422" pageNumber="423">Male.</emphasis>
